---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Link from "../components/Link.astro";
const pageTitle = 'Lyle Klyne'
const employer = `NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory`
const employerURL = `https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/`
---
<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
	<h2 class='summary'>I'm designing software at <Link url={employerURL} text={employer} />, where I work on tools supporting mission planning, sequencing and spacecraft visualization for <a href='https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/' target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Mars 2020</a> and <a href='https://europa.nasa.gov/' target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Europa Clipper</a>.</h2>
	<p>I spend a lot of my time designing digital tools and interactive experiences, and I also making art, furniture, lights and sounds.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Design for an open-source <Link url='https://github.com/NASA-AMMOS/aerie' text='framework for modeling spacecraft' /> with a lot of great people at JPL.</li>
		<li>Design for a science targeting and terrain visualization tools <Link url='https://youtu.be/4OY0YCdFDpU?t=2323' text='ASTTRO' /> & <Link url='https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/mars-virtual-reality-software-wins-nasa-award' text='OnSight' /> â€” used on daily operations for Perseverance and Opportunity.</li>
		<li>A simplified public version of the Mars terrain visualization tools above with WebXR support: <Link url="https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/surface-experience/?drive=1222\&site=26" text='Explore with Perseverance' /> </li>
		<li>An open-source design system to support data-rich and complex patterns common in spacecraft planning: <Link url="https://github.com/nasa-jpl/stellar" text='Stellar Design System' /> </li>
	</ul>

</BaseLayout>